summary: I wish we would drop the habit of telling people "Don't cry." Because crying is good for you. It's a stress reliever and it...
body: I wish we would drop the habit of telling people “Don’t cry.” Because crying is good for you. It’s a stress reliever and it helps purge sickness from the body. It’s healthy to cry. Not to mention when people tell me, “Don’t cry,” like, sorry but I can’t just turn my tears off like a faucet. It doesn’t work like that. Instead we should say, “It’s okay to cry. Let it out.” Yeah, crying can suck but not all crying is bad.

title: BTS Reactions - Eating Disorder
body:
A/N: I hope this is what you hoped for when you said closure ♥️  

Warnings: Talk about eating disorder (angst)

Jin

“I made you your favorite dish,” Jin announced as he placed the plate in front of you. You glanced from the delicious looking chicken to his hopeful eyes as a knot formed in your throat.

“Thank you,” you croaked, “But I can’t eat anything right now.”

The smile on his lips faltered as he slipped into the chair next to you, “You didn’t eat the lunch I made for you either,” he reminded you – as if you didn’t already know.

His hands wrapped around yours, which had begun trembling slightly.

“I’m trying to eat a little healthier,” you explained, your voice cracking halfway.

His gaze shifted between your eyes, as if looking for an unspoken word from you, “I’ll go cook you something a little healthier then.”

He smiled weakly at you, “Thank you,” you whispered, granting him a slight smile.

Hoseok

“You know if you ever have something you want to talk about I’m here, right?” Hobi told you as he leaned against the door frame, looking at you with a curious gaze.

“Of course,” you replied as he dumped down on the couch next to you.

“Then why don’t you?” he asked, trying not to sound too accusing – he hated making you uncomfortable.

“I always do,” you argued, but the lie was obvious.

He intertwined your fingers and stroked his thumb across the back of your hand, “I’m not going to make you tell me what you’re dealing with,” he said, “But I want to be there for you through it all, okay?”

You felt a little less heavy around your heart as you replied, “Okay.”

Namjoon

“Have you lost weight?” Namjoon questioned suddenly, startling you – maybe a bit more than it should have. Your eyes stared down at your own body. Had you lost weight? You supposed you had maybe lost a few pounds.

Your gaze lifted to meet his, which was full of concern, “I don’t think so,” you murmured dismissively.

He wasn’t convinced, “That shirt used to fit you,” he commented, “Now it looks like it’s swallowing you.”

You didn’t get the chance to speak before he twisted toward you, ignoring the episode of Breaking Bad he’d just been very invested in, “What did you have for lunch today?”

Your stomach contracted just at hearing the word lunch, but you couldn’t tell if it was because it made you nauseous or something completely different. “Nothing,” you admitted.

His eyebrows were now knitted together as if he was in pain, “You have to eat, baby.”

“I am eating,” you argued.

“Is there something you want to tell me?” he asked, dismissing your argument.

You weren’t sure if you did or not, his words seemed so strange to you. You did eat… occasionally.

“You don’t have to if you don’t want to,” he added quickly, sensing the change of atmosphere around you, “Just know if you need to talk to someone, I’m right here… always.”

Jimin

His thumbs stroked your puffy, red cheeks, wiping away the tears streaming down your face. He looked at you exactly like he always had, full of love.

“It’ll be okay y/n,” he assured you, “I know it doesn’t seem like that right now, but it will.”

There was a distinct pain in his voice as he spoke.

You noticed that his eyes were red too, and his tears were dangerously close to falling.

A shaky breath whistled through your teeth, “How do you know?” you questioned.

He moved closer and leaned his forehead against yours, closing his eyes tightly, letting the tears roll down his cheeks while breathing heavily.

“I have been there myself” he admitted, shocking you, “And I know how hard it is to say, so thank you.”

Your brows draw together as you tried to catch his gaze, “What are you thanking me for?”

He met your eyes, and a soft smile tugged at the corners of his mouth, “For trusting me.”

Taehyung

Before going into the bedroom where he knew you’d be sleeping, he momentarily stopped in the kitchen, eyeing the fridge.

With a slight sigh, he opened it and stared at the purple container, which hadn’t been opened, neither had the other containers he’d put in there the previous night. Every time he had to stay at the studio overnight he would prepare some food for you. Something easy to heat up in the microwave.

However, this was the fourth time he’d gotten home, and seen that it hadn’t been eaten.

As he slowly made his way to the sink, he silently hoped that you had just ordered a pizza or something.

The garbage bin under the sink was empty, and he knew you hadn’t gone out with the trash because he’d done that yesterday.

His deep exhale broke the silence, as he shut his eyes. It wasn’t like he hadn’t noticed you skipping meals, he just hadn’t wanted to admit that it was true.

He went into the bedroom where you were sleeping on the bed. The blanket was barely covering you, and he could see parts of your exposed skin. It wasn’t hard to tell that you’d lost weight.

When he got into bed, he pulled you tightly against his chest, without you waking up, muttering something into your hair.

“I love you, sweetheart,” he whispered. This wouldn’t change anything, even though he knew that was what you were afraid of.

Yoongi

His eyes widened slightly as the words had left your lips in a hurry, fast enough to make it almost impossible to understand. However, he had understood.

His mouth was agape as if he was about to say something, but he just couldn’t find the words.

You waited for him to react. You couldn’t tell if he was angry, concerned or disappointed by the way he was staring blankly at you.

Your gaze dropped to your feet, which seemed to break his trance.

“Baby,” he muttered under his breath, before wrapping his arms tightly around you.

A sigh of relief escaped your lips as you listened to his soothing words, “I’m glad you told me,” he said, kissing your forehead, “Listen, this won’t change anything, and I know that’s why you haven’t said anything.”

He put a little space between you and caught your gaze, “I still love you, and I’m staying by your side through this okay?”

You felt your eyes fill with unshed tears as you nodded, “Okay.”  

Jungkook

You stopped dead in your tracks as your eyes lifted from your computer to Jungkook, who was struggling to get inside without dropping anything.

He was carrying at least eight different books in his arms. He practically threw them onto the kitchen counter and exhaled loudly.

You pulled one of the books over to you out of pure curiosity, “What’s this?” you asked, before reading the title out loud, “Real Korean cooking.”

From where you were sitting you could see a few more titles, Easy home cooking, Traditional Italian dishes.

“I bought a bunch of cooking books,” he told you, stating the obvious.

One of your eyebrows rose in a questioning look, “Why? You don’t know how to cook.”

He picked up one of the books, playing with the red string attached to it, “I was hoping if I learned how to cook, you would eat it,” he looked guilty standing there as if he’d done something wrong.

“I know you’ve lost weight y/n,” he mumbled, “And I just want to make sure you eat regularly.”

You knew he’d notice at some point, even the jeans you were wearing right now used to be a little too tight, and now they, well… weren’t.

You swallowed hard, “I’ll eat it.”

A bright smile lit up his face, making him look a little boy.

- Calla

“I made you your favorite dish,” Jin announced as he placed the plate in front of you. You glanced from the delicious looking chicken to his hopeful eyes as a knot formed in your throat.

“Thank you,” you croaked, “But I can’t eat anything right now.”

The smile on his lips faltered as he slipped into the chair next to you, “You didn’t eat the lunch I made for you either,” he reminded you – as if you didn’t already know.

His hands wrapped around yours, which had begun trembling slightly.

“I’m trying to eat a little healthier,” you explained, your voice cracking halfway.

His gaze shifted between your eyes, as if looking for an unspoken word from you, “I’ll go cook you something a little healthier then.”

He smiled weakly at you, “Thank you,” you whispered, granting him a slight smile.

Hoseok

“You know if you ever have something you want to talk about I’m here, right?” Hobi told you as he leaned against the door frame, looking at you with a curious gaze.

“Of course,” you replied as he dumped down on the couch next to you.

“Then why don’t you?” he asked, trying not to sound too accusing – he hated making you uncomfortable.

“I always do,” you argued, but the lie was obvious.

He intertwined your fingers and stroked his thumb across the back of your hand, “I’m not going to make you tell me what you’re dealing with,” he said, “But I want to be there for you through it all, okay?”

You felt a little less heavy around your heart as you replied, “Okay.”

Namjoon

“Have you lost weight?” Namjoon questioned suddenly, startling you – maybe a bit more than it should have. Your eyes stared down at your own body. Had you lost weight? You supposed you had maybe lost a few pounds.

Your gaze lifted to meet his, which was full of concern, “I don’t think so,” you murmured dismissively.

He wasn’t convinced, “That shirt used to fit you,” he commented, “Now it looks like it’s swallowing you.”

You didn’t get the chance to speak before he twisted toward you, ignoring the episode of Breaking Bad he’d just been very invested in, “What did you have for lunch today?”

Your stomach contracted just at hearing the word lunch, but you couldn’t tell if it was because it made you nauseous or something completely different. “Nothing,” you admitted.

His eyebrows were now knitted together as if he was in pain, “You have to eat, baby.”

“I am eating,” you argued.

“Is there something you want to tell me?” he asked, dismissing your argument.

You weren’t sure if you did or not, his words seemed so strange to you. You did eat… occasionally.

“You don’t have to if you don’t want to,” he added quickly, sensing the change of atmosphere around you, “Just know if you need to talk to someone, I’m right here… always.”

Jimin

His thumbs stroked your puffy, red cheeks, wiping away the tears streaming down your face. He looked at you exactly like he always had, full of love.

“It’ll be okay y/n,” he assured you, “I know it doesn’t seem like that right now, but it will.”

There was a distinct pain in his voice as he spoke.

You noticed that his eyes were red too, and his tears were dangerously close to falling.

A shaky breath whistled through your teeth, “How do you know?” you questioned.

He moved closer and leaned his forehead against yours, closing his eyes tightly, letting the tears roll down his cheeks while breathing heavily.

“I have been there myself” he admitted, shocking you, “And I know how hard it is to say, so thank you.”

Your brows draw together as you tried to catch his gaze, “What are you thanking me for?”

He met your eyes, and a soft smile tugged at the corners of his mouth, “For trusting me.”

Taehyung

Before going into the bedroom where he knew you’d be sleeping, he momentarily stopped in the kitchen, eyeing the fridge.

With a slight sigh, he opened it and stared at the purple container, which hadn’t been opened, neither had the other containers he’d put in there the previous night. Every time he had to stay at the studio overnight he would prepare some food for you. Something easy to heat up in the microwave.

However, this was the fourth time he’d gotten home, and seen that it hadn’t been eaten.

As he slowly made his way to the sink, he silently hoped that you had just ordered a pizza or something.

The garbage bin under the sink was empty, and he knew you hadn’t gone out with the trash because he’d done that yesterday.

His deep exhale broke the silence, as he shut his eyes. It wasn’t like he hadn’t noticed you skipping meals, he just hadn’t wanted to admit that it was true.

He went into the bedroom where you were sleeping on the bed. The blanket was barely covering you, and he could see parts of your exposed skin. It wasn’t hard to tell that you’d lost weight.

When he got into bed, he pulled you tightly against his chest, without you waking up, muttering something into your hair.

“I love you, sweetheart,” he whispered. This wouldn’t change anything, even though he knew that was what you were afraid of.

Yoongi

His eyes widened slightly as the words had left your lips in a hurry, fast enough to make it almost impossible to understand. However, he had understood.

His mouth was agape as if he was about to say something, but he just couldn’t find the words.

You waited for him to react. You couldn’t tell if he was angry, concerned or disappointed by the way he was staring blankly at you.

Your gaze dropped to your feet, which seemed to break his trance.

“Baby,” he muttered under his breath, before wrapping his arms tightly around you.

A sigh of relief escaped your lips as you listened to his soothing words, “I’m glad you told me,” he said, kissing your forehead, “Listen, this won’t change anything, and I know that’s why you haven’t said anything.”

He put a little space between you and caught your gaze, “I still love you, and I’m staying by your side through this okay?”

You felt your eyes fill with unshed tears as you nodded, “Okay.”  

Jungkook

You stopped dead in your tracks as your eyes lifted from your computer to Jungkook, who was struggling to get inside without dropping anything.

He was carrying at least eight different books in his arms. He practically threw them onto the kitchen counter and exhaled loudly.

You pulled one of the books over to you out of pure curiosity, “What’s this?” you asked, before reading the title out loud, “Real Korean cooking.”

From where you were sitting you could see a few more titles, Easy home cooking, Traditional Italian dishes.

“I bought a bunch of cooking books,” he told you, stating the obvious.

One of your eyebrows rose in a questioning look, “Why? You don’t know how to cook.”

He picked up one of the books, playing with the red string attached to it, “I was hoping if I learned how to cook, you would eat it,” he looked guilty standing there as if he’d done something wrong.

“I know you’ve lost weight y/n,” he mumbled, “And I just want to make sure you eat regularly.”

You knew he’d notice at some point, even the jeans you were wearing right now used to be a little too tight, and now they, well… weren’t.

You swallowed hard, “I’ll eat it.”

A bright smile lit up his face, making him look a little boy.
